===Etymology 1===
{{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|plesen|plesen, plaisen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|plaise|lang=fro}}, conjugated form of {{term|plaisir|lang=fro}} or {{term|plaire|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|placeo|placēre|lang=la|to please, to seem good}}<ref name="dictionary">{{R:Dictionary.com}}</ref>, from the {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*plā-k-||wide and flat}}. Displaced native {{etyl|enm|-}} {{term|quemen|quemen, queamen|to please|lang=enm}} (from {{etyl|ang|-}} {{m|ang|cwēman||to please}}), {{etyl|enm|-}} {{term|biluvien||to please, delight|lang=enm}} (from {{etyl|enm|-}} {{term|be-|bi-, be-|lang=enm}} + {{term|luvien||to love|lang=enm}}), {{etyl|enm|-}} {{term|liken||to like, please|lang=enm}} (from {{etyl|ang|-}} {{m|ang|līcian||to please, be like}}), {{etyl|enm|-}} {{term|lusten|lusten, listen|to be pleasing, delight|lang=enm}} (from {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|lystan||to please|lang=ang}}).

